The paper deals with out-of-distribution detection in neural networks processing images, which is a problem commonly addressed in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of metric learning is a key aspect of the proposed approach, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed method in terms of classification accuracy, which is a common topic in computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper mentions the application of the proposed method to traffic sign recognition, which is a specific problem in neural networks (cs.NE).
